  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer, utilizing their position as an accountant to exploit the company's financial systems. This abuse of fiduciary duty warrants a period of incarceration to serve as a punishment and deterrent. However, several mitigating factors have been taken into consideration. The defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating that this behavior is an isolated deviation rather than a pattern of criminality. Furthermore, the defendant has made efforts to right their wrong by paying back a portion of the embezzled funds before sentencing. Balancing the severity of the breach of trust against the defendant's lack of criminal history and partial restitution, a moderate custodial sentence is appropriate. A 12-month sentence ensures accountability while acknowledging the mitigating circumstances.",
  "verdict": 12
}
